title: Average Weekly Earnings, First Class Railroad Employees, Unskilled Labor for United States
notes:
For Method Of Computation See Description Of Series. July 1930-1932 Data Were Computed By NBER By The Same Method. A 10% Pay Cut Occured February 1, 1932. For Cuts Before And After See Statistics Of Railways, Icc, 1932, P. 5-26. Source: Computed By The National Industrial Conference Board From Data In "Wage Statistics", Interstate Commerce Commission.
